title: Deviled Eggs
directions: Place eggs in a large wide saucepan and cover with cold water. Bring to a boil for 20 minutes. Remove eggs and and cool with ice. Remove shells from eggs and slice in half lengthwise. Separate egg yolks and place into a bowl. Place whites on a separate plate. Add mayo, mustard, and salt to taste, to yolks and mash together with a fork until creamy and smooth. Using a large star tip and resealable plastic bag, pipe the yolk mixture back into each egg, enough to fill yolk holes completely. Dust tops with paprika. Refrigerate. Serve cold.
